MoD survey

Sam Langton & Reka Solymosi

19/01/2022

Motivation

Do people make worse estimates about the underlying data when observing the original boundaries of a map, in comparison to alternative methods (e.g., dorling cartograms, hex grids)?

Data

  • Index of Multiple Deprivation (2019)
  • Lower Super Output Areas nested within Local Authorities
  • Three of the top 10 most deprived Local Authorities
    • Birmingham
    • Hartelpool
    • Burnley
  • Recoded 1-10 scale to 1-5
  • Three map types:
    • Orignal
    • Hex grids (geogrid)
    • Dorling cartogram (cartogram)


Survey

Results

Data

  • MS Forms (thanks, Nat!).
  • Respondents given ~roughly 24 hours to complete the survey.
  • 70 individual responses.
  • 2 respondent dropped because they were tests.
  • 2 respondents dropped due to text answers.
    • Sorry
    • Still very useful information.
  • 2 respondents dropped for not providing answer(s).
  • 64 respondents used in analyses.
